  abstract = {Aims: We report the discovery of very shallow ($\Delta$ F/F \textasciitilde{} 3.4\texttimes{} 10-4), periodic dips in the light curve of an active V = 11.7 G9V star observed by the CoRoT satellite, which we interpret as caused by a transiting companion. We describe the 3-colour CoRoT data and complementary ground-based observations that support the planetary nature of the companion. Methods: We used CoRoT colours
