(b and c); three additional few-Earth mass candidates with periods of 92, 62, and 39 days (d, e and f); a cold super-Earth in a 260-day
orbit (g) and tantalizing evidence of a $\sim$1 M$\oplus$ object in a close-in orbit of 17 days (h). We explore whether long-term stable orbits are
